---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Amir Ranjbar — CS graduate, software engineer, based in Toronto.">
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>About</h1>
  </header>

  <div class="prose mb-section">
    <p>
      I'm Amir — a computer science graduate based in Toronto. I finished my B.Sc. at
      Toronto Metropolitan University in 2025, and I'm currently focused on breaking into
      the tech industry as a software engineer.
    </p>

    <p>
      My background is in full-stack development with a lean toward backend systems.
      I've worked with Python, JavaScript, SQL, Docker, and PostgreSQL across internships
      and personal projects. I care about writing clean code, understanding systems deeply,
      and building things that actually work.
    </p>

    <h2>What I'm doing now</h2>

    <p>
      Right now I'm in the thick of the job search, which means a lot of my time goes
      toward interview prep — data structures, algorithms, system design — and building
      projects that let me apply what I'm learning. This blog is part of that process.
      Writing about what I'm studying forces me to understand it properly, and it gives
      me something to point to that shows how I think.
    </p>

    <p>
      I started this site because I wanted a space that's mine — not a LinkedIn post,
      not a tweet, just a place to document what I'm learning and building without any
      character limits or algorithms deciding who sees it.
    </p>

    <h2>Background</h2>

    <p>
      Before and during university, I interned at a couple of companies. At RWS Group,
      I worked on automating data preprocessing pipelines across multiple languages.
      At Pyypl, I worked on containerizing development environments and optimizing
      database performance. Both taught me a lot about working in real codebases and
      shipping things that other people depend on.
    </p>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>

    <p>
      I'm always open to conversations about tech, opportunities, or collaboration.
      Best way to reach me is <a href="mailto:a77ranjbar@gmail.com">email</a> or
      <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/amir-ranjbar" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      You can see what I'm building on <a href="https://github.com/ax00z" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
